{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_013H7DeU2TMj5ZjRiCExaTxS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy.\n\n## Summary\n\nA 3-node CockroachDB cluster is running in the `cockroachdb` namespace using only native Kubernetes resources (manifest: `crdb.yaml`).\n\n**Resources created:**\n- **Headless Service** `crdb-cluster` (`clusterIP: None`, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) — provides stable pod DNS for peering. Exposes grpc/26257 + http/8080.\n- **Public Service** `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP) — client/UI entrypoint. Same two ports.\n- **StatefulSet** `crdb-cluster` — 3 replicas, image `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0`, each pod advertises its own DNS (`$(hostname).crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`) and joins all three nodes via `--join`. Insecure mode (`--insecure`, no TLS).\n- **VolumeClaimTemplate** `datadir` — 10Gi RWO per pod (all 3 PVCs Bound).\n- **PodDisruptionBudget** `crdb-cluster-pdb` — `maxUnavailable: 1`, so voluntary disruptions can only evict one node at a time, preserving quorum (2 of 3 always available). Plus soft pod anti-affinity to spread across nodes.\n\n**Constraints honored:** existing `crdb-cluster-sa` ServiceAccount reused (no new RBAC), no CRDs/operator, exact names and ports as specified.\n\n**Verification:**\n- StatefulSet `3/3` Ready; all pods `1/1 Running`.\n- One-time `cockroach init` performed (required to bootstrap a fresh cluster — without it pod-0 stays NotReady and the OrderedReady StatefulSet won't progress).\n- `cockroach node status` shows all 3 nodes `is_available=true`, `is_live=true`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2112,"cache_read_input_tokens":33606,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2112},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnos